# Adding a New Tenant

> **Maintenance**: Update this file when the new-tenant steps or scripts change (`rules-sync.mdc`).

## Required steps

1. Create `src/tenants/{tenant-id}/config.ts` — `TenantConfig` (`id`, `name`, `domains`, `locales`, `features`, `theme`, `dataAdapter`)
2. Create `src/tenants/{tenant-id}/blocks/index.ts` — `registerTenantBlocks("{tenant-id}", { … })`
3. Create `src/tenants/{tenant-id}/templates/` — at least `default.tsx` (header/footer via `getNavigationCached`); optional `bare.tsx`, `detail.tsx`
4. Create `src/tenants/{tenant-id}/blocks/header/header.tsx` and `blocks/footer/footer.tsx`
5. Create mock data under `src/core/mock-data.ts/{folder}/` — `pages/home.json`, `navigation.json`, `sitemap.json` as needed (`{folder}` = tenant id, or a short name like `resort`)
6. Add `pnpm` scripts in `package.json`: `dev:{short}`, `build:{short}`, `lint:{short}` with `TENANT_ID={tenant-id}`
7. Add CI matrix entry for `tenant_id` in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` if the tenant should lint in PRs
8. Create **`.cursor/rules/tenants/{tenant-id}/catalog.mdc`** — document all blocks, templates, pages, integrations (copy structure from an existing tenant catalog)
9. Add **`deploy-{short}.yml`** + Vercel project + secrets — see `deployment.mdc`

Block registration is automatic: root `app/layout.tsx` imports `@core/init`, which imports `@tenant/blocks` (no manual `init.ts` list per tenant).

If `mock-data` folder name ≠ tenant id, document mapping in `scripts/prepare-tenant.js` and the tenant catalog.

## Tenant config shape

```typescript
import type { TenantConfig } from "@core/types/tenant";

const config: TenantConfig = {
  id: "my-tenant",
  name: "My Site",
  domains: ["my-site.localhost"],
  defaultLocale: "en",
  locales: ["en"],
  features: {
    blog: false,
    booking: false,
    reviews: false,
    search: false,
    newsletter: false,
  },
  theme: {
    colors: {
      primary: "#000000",
      secondary: "#666666",
      accent: "#0066cc",
      background: "#ffffff",
      foreground: "#111111",
      muted: "#f4f4f5",
      border: "#e4e4e7",
      textPrimary: "#111111",
    },
    fonts: {
      heading: "var(--font-inter)",
      body: "var(--font-inter)",
    },
    borderRadius: "0.375rem",
  },
  dataAdapter: "mock",
};

export default config;
```

## After any later change

Update affected rules per `rules-sync.mdc` (including the new tenant `catalog.mdc`).

## Testing

```bash
pnpm dev:{short}    # e.g. dev:bike, dev:resort
pnpm lint:{short}   # if added
TENANT_ID={tenant-id} pnpm type-check
```
